cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CC

This paper deals with a network of spiking neurons and proposes three problems related to neural coding and information processing. The paper is likely to be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with neural networks and their behavior. It could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper proposes solutions to problems related to information processing. Additionally, the paper could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it deals with a system of spiking neurons and their behavior. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as the paper discusses lower bounds for the time and number of neurons required to solve the proposed problems.
